                                   Poison
                                   ======

Introduction
------------
Purpose of this document is to explain and document the ongoing additions
of various poisons to the game.

Definitions
-----------
Meal/Keg/Food/Alcohol Poisons - These are what will be referred to as 
           Ingested poisons.  These poisons are a one-time damage, with
	   no lingering effect.  They can and will kill the victim if 
	   they are too low on health.


Existing Methods of Delivery
----------------------------
Currently there are the following devices in the game to deliver Poisons:

A dull grey jar  Can be purchased in the Thief Guild poison hall. Is 
	 	 capable of delivering ingested poisons. One use per
		 keg or meal, 3 uses for drinks or foods. Reverses
		 healing effects of item.

Regulations
-----------
Poisons are not to affect NPK players.  Ingested poisons have been written
to support NPK checks, keeping them from ingesting the contaminated 
substance at all, with no loss to uses.

Code Support
------------
The code in the ingested poisons allow for future implementations of
purification spells or abilities. The following call applies:

void set_purified()

When called on the contaminated item, it will be restored to original
healing values.  

*Note* Purification isn't to be easy.  The cost for ingested poisons
are steep and making purification easy is very counter-productive
to mud balance.

You can query any ingested poison object with int query_poisoned() and it
will return 1 if the item is contaminated, null if not.

When actually poisoning an ingested substance, you can use set_poisoned()
to throw the query_poisoned() flag and save old healing values which, as
mentioned, can be restored via set_purified().  Actual modifying of the
healing values of the ingested items are modified using:

set_hp_heal(int arg) and set_sp_heal(int arg)

